We first compute the average total assets using the beginning and ending amounts from the balance sheet:

  Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
    = (13,000,000.00 + 14,879,933.86) / 2  
    = 27,879,933.86 / 2  
    = 13,939,966.93

Next, we take the Net Profit from the income statement, which is –1,175,062.19.

Then, the Return on Assets (ROA) is calculated as:

  ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%  
    = (–1,175,062.19 / 13,939,966.93) × 100%  
    ≈ –8.44%

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "-8.44%"
  }
}
